#compdef x-cmd
# Documentation: https://github.com/x-cmd/x-cmd
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-21
# Verified: upstream docs at the URL above.
# STUB: x-cmd is a modular shell toolbox (~300 modules) invoked as
# `x <module>` or `x-cmd <module>`. README/start guide do not document any
# top-level CLI flags like --help or --version, so no flags are claimed
# here. Subcommands include env, upgrade, plus dozens of per-module
# entrypoints (gh, gt, gl, bwh, shodan, tldr, claude, openai, gemini,
# deepseek, env, top, ps, ls, cd, etc.) but these are too dynamic to
# enumerate without fabrication.

local curcontext="$curcontext" state line ret=1
_arguments -s -S \
  '*::module:_default' && ret=0
return ret
